summary: The Avengers au where everything's the same but Tony misheard Loki's name as Larry
body:
The Avengers au where everything’s the same but Tony misheard Loki’s name as Larry

Thor: Any parting words before I take my brother home?

Everyone:

Tony, dead serious: You’re going to f*cking jail, Larry.

Everyone: *starts cracking up*

Tony: What. What’s funny?

Clint, wheezing: It’s Loki.

Tony: You mean to tell me this entire time I thought that a-hole’s name was Larry and you all let me roll with it?

Steve, with a smug grin: Uh huh.

Nat: Yep.

Tony: And everytime I said Larry on the f*cking comms-

Bruce: The signal wasn’t bad, we just kept turning them off because we were laughing.

Tony: Wow.

Tony: Avengers cancelled, I’m going back to solo stuff.

blog.description: King of all Dragons, Death, Drugs,

body:
Nobody’s Hero

When I was told that I was going to become a hero, I kinda laughed at it and rolled my eyes. I knew that I’d never be a hero.. Well at least to anyone. I believed it even more when they decided to start experimenting on me. I hated it.. Laying there while they poked at me with needles and hosing me down with ice water. I thought it couldn’t get any worse until they knocked me out and pretty much opened up my chest to fuse some damn stone into my heart.. That was hell. Because even while I was out, I could still feel them take the blade and feel the cold metal rip slowly through my skin and the burning pain of the stone becoming part of my still beating heart…  When I came to I found out the my mutations were activated and I was some super freak.. But I wasn’t the only one there, there was a man named Wade who I pretty much became good friends with. So when the fire erupted, I used my new abilities and got out of there.. Well not before I helped Wade peel himself off a metal rod. After parting ways I made my way into Manhattan, I get recruited by a man with a eye patch named Nick and he pretty much told me that I was going to be part of his team.. I didn’t argue there. So this is where my adventure of “becoming a hero” started I guess.

A preview of the introduction. I kinda think that its pretty good.. Kinda
